  "prompt": "How do you find a good doctor?",
  "response": "Here are some tips for finding a good doctor:\n\n1. Check credentials and board certification\n- Verify medical license\n- Confirm board certification in their specialty\n\n2. Consider insurance and network coverage\n- Check which doctors are in your insurance network\n- Understand potential out-of-pocket costs\n\n3. Read patient reviews and ratings\n- Check online review sites\n- Ask friends and family for recommendations\n\n4. Consider location and accessibility\n- Proximity to your home/work\n- Office hours and availability\n- Ease of scheduling appointments\n\n5. Verify hospital affiliations\n- Check which hospitals the doctor is associated with\n- Ensure hospitals have good reputations\n\n6. Assess communication style\n- Schedule an initial consultation\n- Evaluate how comfortable you feel with the doctor\n- Check if they listen and explain things clearly\n\n7. Check experience and specialization\n- Research their background\n- Look for expertise in your specific health needs\n\n8. Ask for referrals\n- Consult your primary care physician\n- Get recommendations from other healthcare professionals\n\n9. Consider language and cultural compatibility\n- Ensure effective communication\n- Find a doctor who understands your cultural background\n\n10. Trust your instincts\n- Choose a doctor you feel comfortable with\n- Don't hesitate to switch if you're not satisfied",
